{
  "text": "Rarer techniques such as endoscopic urethroplasty with a skin or mucosal flap with different fixation mechanisms have the advantage of being less invasive, but not sufficiently studied to talk about their success. Preliminary data are contradictory -the effectiveness was from 54.5 to 80 % [CITATION_1] 31] endoscopic antegrade urethroplasty was performed in 11 patients with recurrent vesicourethral anastomotic strictures that developed after retropubic radical prostatectomy (RRP.",
